[1] Texas
Date: Wed 24 Sep 2014
Source: Texas Animal Health Commission [edited]
http://www.tahc.state.tx.us/news/pr/2014/2014-09-24_VSUpdates.pdf


Vesicular Stomatitis (VS) in Texas Update
-----------------------------------------
Since the [17 Sep 2014] update, the Texas Animal Health Commission (TAHC) received confirmation of one new case of vesicular stomatitis (VS) in horses. The premises is located 13 miles southeast of Bastrop in Bastrop County.

Of the 62 premises, 50 premises have been released. Seven counties have been released from quarantine: Jim Wells, Kinney, Nueces , San Patricio, Val Verde, Williamson, and Hidalgo counties.

The newly identified infected premises are currently under quarantine by the TAHC. Affected horses will be monitored by regulatory veterinarians while under quarantine. Premises are eligible for quarantine release 21 days after all lesions have healed.

--
Communicated by:
Callie McNulty
Texas Animal Health Commission
<callie.mcnulty@tahc.texas.gov>

